An **optional starter** for the deliverable of a `documentation`-kind project (see `### Project kind` in `workflow/project-kind.md`) — a reference document (guide / spec / explainer) with no executable code. Copy it into `deliverable/` as a seed when the deliverable *is* a reference doc; it is one documentation shape among many, never a mandated scaffold. Written for the reader and read by agents before planning any change to the document.

> Reader **experience flow** lives in `docs/user-journeys.md` (what the person is trying to learn / do / where they get stuck) — this guide is **additive**, not a replacement: a journey references, the guide explains. The **good-outcome bar** lives in the feature's Product Contract (Must work / Must not break / Acceptance checks); a reference doc's validation is **editorial review + expert sign-off** (`## Validation: <date> — sign-off — passed`), not a dry-run. Any status enumeration / identifier grammar the text would name lives **once** in `docs/architecture.md` `## Behavioral contract (taxonomies & invariants)` and is referenced here, never restated.
